name: Holiday Inn Express Baltimore-Downtown, an IHG Hotel
description:
Featuring spacious guestrooms furnished with flat-screen TVs and free wireless internet access, this downtown Baltimore hotel provides easy access to area attractions, including the scenic Inner Harbor.
Begin the day at the Holiday Inn Express Baltimore-Downtown with a free hot breakfast buffet or take advantage of in-room coffeemakers, microwaves and mini-refrigerators. Enjoy the on-site fitness center or finish some work with the well-equipped business facilities.
John Hopkins Hospital and Mercy Medical Center are only moments from the Baltimore-Downtown Holiday Inn Express with free shuttle service. The Science Center Museum and Camden Yard Stadium, home to MLB's Orioles are also easily accessible.
breakfast: Continental, Vegetarian, Vegan, Gluten-free, American, Buffet

userReviews.title: Location  is horrid & appears to be actively kept secret.Some staff need development or dismissal.
userReviews.positive: Food service was as expected by this brand of property. Clean presentation and courteous staff. Wider variety - fruit or yogurt -  offered perhaps vs 4-5 types of bread/ bagels .  Coffee & tea options and quality very good.
userReviews.negative:
See above, very poor health & dietary choices ( it is 2022, not 1982 ) 
Front desk staff ranged from totally uninformed about availability of basic services upon check in , to very helpful and willing to go the extra mile. Several day staff ( both Friday AM and Monday at check out ) acted as if I was inconveniencing them when I arrived & departed ….. poor impressions to give at beginning  & at end of stay ( ironically , both younger female staff ) while the evening staff & night managers ( both younger African - American men ) were excellent and courteous as well as knowledgeable when asked service availability questions. As a Canadian I am aware of the social &  economic challenges and conflicts in the US, but I found virtually all your staff to be excellent, with the exception of the day clerk on Friday 10/21 ( who seemed bored and disinterested in my business upon arrival ) and again on Monday 10/24th ( who could barely manage to get off her chair behind the encounter to provide a print out of my bill ) After decades of managing staff from clerks to top managers & sales people, these two individuals need significant training and attitude adjustments, or should be given the opportunity to pursue a new line of employment.
Lastly , of my 3night / 4 day stay my room was “ treated “ to housekeeping ONCE , after I twice requested it .
No apologies , no consideration at checkout or otherwise ( in Canada it is customary to offer either a credit on one’s bill or a voucher for future stay ).  The significant flaws , sadly, overwhelmed the modest pluses of this property

name: Residence Inn by Marriott Baltimore Downtown/ Inner Harbor
description:
Residence Inn Downtown is located next to Baltimore Convention Center and 2 blocks from the renowned Inner Harbor. It features a well-equipped gym and can provide an airport shuttle service.
The spacious rooms at the Residence Inn Baltimore Downtown/Inner Harbor are equipped with free Wi-Fi and a TV set. They all include a large seating/working area and some also offer cooking facilities.
Guests can enjoy a daily menu of American classic dishes at the in-house 17 Light Restaurant. 17 Light is open for lunch, dinner and room service, and features happy hour specials Monday through Friday.
Famous nearby landmarks include the World Trade Center Institute and the popular National Aquarium, both within a 10-minute walk from the Residence Inn Baltimore Downtown hotel.

description:
You're eligible for a Genius discount at Ulysses! To save at this property, all you have to do is sign in.
Located a 6-minute walk from The Walters Art Museum, Ulysses offers 5-star accommodations in Baltimore and features a bar. With a restaurant, the 5-star hotel has air-conditioned rooms with free WiFi, each with a private bathroom. The property provides nightclub and a 24-hour front desk.
All guest rooms in the hotel are equipped with a flat-screen TV with cable channels. At Ulysses every room comes with bed linen and towels.
Breakfast is available daily, and includes à la carte, American and vegetarian options.
Popular points of interest near the accommodation include Baltimore - Penn Station, MD, Historic Ships in Baltimore and Baltimore Convention Center. The nearest airport is Baltimore - Washington International Airport, 10 miles from Ulysses.

userReviews.title: Luxurious, 19th century meets John Waters hotel.
userReviews.positive:
Location is couple of blocks from monument in Mt. Vernon neighborhood.  Charming area with strong LGBTQ presence and historical spaces/buildings.  One of the 'safe' neighborhoods.  Hotel has 2 bars-Ash and Blooms.  Both are a delight on the senses.  Restaurant is in Ash Bar and was 5 star quality.  Room was simply adorable with 4 poster bed, custom thermostat, ample outlets (no USB) and a bathroom with WOW factor!  Staff were friendly and helpful.  Pro tip: parking on street is free beginning 6 pm Saturday and all day Sunday.  Otherwise the meter is $1.75/hour from 8am-6.  There is a garage nearby-not sure of cost.  For anyone over 50, bring your flashlight lol lighting everywhere is dim.  Sets an intimate ambiance but can be challenging finding things like elevator electronic access pad or reading menus.
Nothing 'corporate ' here and amuch needed and welcome change to the typical hotel.  Like Baltimore 's moniker "Charm City", this hotel oozes turn of the century luxury with a hint of the quirky.  Make sure you read the newspaper in your room.  Best horoscopes ever. I suspect John Waters helped write them lol
userReviews.negative: Valet parking is $48!

name: Pier 5 Hotel Baltimore, Curio Collection by Hilton
description:
With a scenic waterfront location close to area attractions, including the National Aquarium, this Baltimore hotel offers free local area shuttles along with delicious on-site dining options.
The Pier 5 Hotel is conveniently located minutes from the Power Plant entertainment complex and the historic Fell's Point neighborhood. The on-site personal concierge service can also help arrange area tours, dinner reservations and much more.
Guests at the Pier 5 can start the day with breakfast and enjoy the weekday evening with hands-on cooking demonstrations. The hotel also features on-site dining at Ruth's Chris Steak House and McCormick & Schmick's.
Cozy guest rooms at the Pier 5 Hotel feature free bottled water, wireless internet access and coffeemakers. Guests will also enjoy on-demand movies and Gilchrist & Soames bath soap.

userReviews.negative: When we arrived (on our anniversary day) the hotel front desk person could not find my reservation. Asked if it was under a different name (it wasnt). Strange attitude, like she couldnt be bothered. THere is a park next to the hotel at the end of hte pier that homeless people sleep in, somewhat unsettling, but the Inner Harbor area itself has a problem with homelessness and drugs so cant blame the hotel. The lock on the balcony door did not lock.  On a couple occasions we had to wait extraordinarily long for an elevator, despite that theres only 2 floors and 2 elevator shafts, and the hotel was not even close to full capacity - we believe the hotel staff was holding the elevator on the lower floors for service since they are double-sided elevators. No other explanation to be waiting 5 minutes for an elevator in that scenario. Some guests may complain about the parking, there is a public lot right next to the hotel and the hotel comps your parking, really not that big of a deal at all just to clarify.

name: Hotel Revival Baltimore, part of JdV by Hyatt
description:
Located in the Mt. Vernon Cultural District of downtown Baltimore, this hotel is adjacent to the Washington Monument and Museum. It offers on-site dining and classical rooms with free WiFi.
Each room at the Hotel Revival Baltimore, part of JdV by Hyatt features warm colors and classical furniture. They include white marble walls in the bathroom and a 32-inch flat-screen TV. A microwave and coffee maker are also provided.
A fitness center and a large library with oriental moldings are part of the facilities.
The on-site restaurant, Topside, serves French-influenced American cuisine for breakfast, lunch, and dinner.
The University of Maryland at Baltimore is a 15-minute walk from Hotel Revival Baltimore, part of JdV by Hyatt. M&T Bank Stadium, home of the Baltimore Ravens, is 1.6 miles from the hotel.

userReviews.title: The Revival is a great place to stay in Baltimore.
userReviews.positive:
We stayed at the Revival for two nights. We have stayed there before and always enjoyed our stay. We had a room on the 14th floor overlooking the Washington Monument. It was a very nice room. The bed was very comfortable. The service was excellent and friendly. The rooftop restaurant is also excellent. 
When we left I accidentally left a pair of Maui Jim  sun glasses behind. When we got home to Atlanta ,my wife called the hotel and asked if they had been found. I fully expected that they would say no. But the person who answered the phone said she would check, and she then said they had been found. Moreover, she offered to mail them to me. Two days later a Fedex package arrived with the glasses. I was thankful and impressed. Clearly this was service above and beyond. The Revival is definitely a great place to stay in Baltimore.

userReviews.title: Great Suite with amazing views.
userReviews.positive: we stayed in the executive king suite and it was simply amazing. The room was big and spacious with amazing views. The bathroom was also great, with a big bath and great shower. Sofa and window seats were also comfortable and well located.

I think the room must have been right next to a boiler room because I could hear a loud machine followed by flowing water sounds about every half hour or so, which made it difficult to sleep.

userReviews.title: Beautiful place in a nice location

name: SpringHill Suites by Marriott Baltimore Downtown Convention Center Area
description:
You're eligible for a Genius discount at SpringHill Suites by Marriott Baltimore Downtown Convention Center Area! To save at this property, all you have to do is sign in.
Located in Baltimore and with Sports Legends Museum at Camden Yards reachable within a 8-minute walk, SpringHill Suites by Marriott Baltimore Downtown Convention Center Area has express check-in and check-out, non-smoking rooms, a fitness center, free WiFi and a shared lounge. Popular points of interest nearby include Historic Ships in Baltimore, Edgar Allen Poe Museum and Inner Harbor. Private parking can be arranged at an extra charge.
The hotel offers a buffet or American breakfast.
SpringHill Suites by Marriott Baltimore Downtown Convention Center Area also provides a business center and guests can use the fax machine and photocopier at the accommodation. SpringHill Suites by Marriott Baltimore Downtown Convention Center Area can conveniently provide information at the reception to help guests to get around the area.
Popular points of interest near the hotel include Baltimore Convention Center, University of Maryland – Baltimore and The Walters Art Museum. The nearest airport is Baltimore - Washington International Airport, 8.7 miles from SpringHill Suites by Marriott Baltimore Downtown Convention Center Area.

name: Baltimore Marriott Inner Harbor at Camden Yards
description:
This downtown Baltimore hotel is within a 3-minute drive of the Inner Harbor. The hotel offers a fitness center, and rooms with flat-screen TVs. Free WiFi is available in public areas.
Rooms at Baltimore Marriott Inner Harbor at Camden Yards include a work desk and a coffee maker. The rooms are equipped with a seating area.
Dining options at the Baltimore Marriott include The Yard , which features American cuisine.
Inner Harbor Marriott is within a 6-minute walk of the Oriole Park at Camden Yard, and just 0.6 mi from M&T Bank Stadium. The Baltimore Convention Center is 2 blocks from the hotel.

userReviews.title: A great choice for exploring Mount Vernon
userReviews.positive: I had a conference in a hotel along the Inner Harbor and wanted to spend a day before returning home exploring the Mount Vernon neighborhood. The Indigo seemed to be in a good location to do that, and it was cheaper than the alternatives when I booked. I walked the few blocks north to the hotel on arrival (through Baltimore's rather scuzzy downtown business district) and then took the light rail to the airport from Centre Street when leaving. Convenient. The Roman Catholic Cathedral is across the street, and all of Mount Vernon (and numerous bars and restaurants) is right there. Lexington Market is just a few minutes away. I felt safe, although a 7-Eleven nearby was robbed on the morning I left. . . . My room was comfortable and had a great view over the rooftops toward the Washington Monument. I didn't try the restaurant, except to have a quick drink at the bar, but it looked good. Staff members were friendly, funny, and helpful. I would've liked to have stayed longer.
userReviews.negative: The hotel really served my needs well. No complaints.

The best part of the hotel is the restaurant/bar located in lobby, well decorated.
Complimentary breakfast ((tax, tips excluded) is À la carte, can select from the menu or pay extra for an upgrade.
userReviews.negative:
like everything.
However, there was an Fire alarm incident during our stay. （Fortunately everybody's safe, no real damage. ）
around minutes passed midnight, the fire alarm was loudly alarming inside our room/hall, basically everywhere. 
We were asleep already, but of course woke up and walked stairs to lobby. 
The most confusing part is the hotel staffs didn't give enough instructions or some action to calm or direct the hotel guests, children, mom with baby, elderly accumulated in the lobby, some guests were actual outside the building (it's cold but that suppose to be the right thing to do) many of them also confusing and ask around or not taking serious enough. 
Just a quick share, we knew the staffs should be very busy at the moment (thank you still) and it was not a drill, but fire alarm can be really crucial. 
Wishing the hotel can manage more professionally if happen in the future, at least calm people down(by words or put a board written the situation or so) or give more clear instruction.

description:
Surrounded by some of Baltimore's most popular sites and ideally connect to the Convention Center, this Inner Harbor hotel offers modern amenities and completely nonsmoking guestrooms.
The Sheraton Inner Harbor offers an ideal location within walking distance of Oriole Park at Camden Yards, the National Aquarium and the Maryland Science Center. The hotel's knowledgeable concierge services can also arrange area tours, dinner reservations, tickets and more.
Contemporary accommodations at the Inner Harbor Sheraton feature signature Sweet Sleeper beds, flat-screen TVs and wireless internet access. Guests can also enjoy in-room coffeemakers with Starbucks coffee.
The Sheraton at the Inner Harbor features a state-of-the-art on-site fitness facilities. Car rental services as well as a gift shop are also available on-site.

userReviews.title: Overall, our one night stay was great!
userReviews.positive:
We liked that the Sheraton was so close to the MARC, which we rode up from WDC.  Since we were only there overnight, it was very close to the Inner Harbor and we were able to walk to dinner and enjoy an evening walk afterwards!
We had a corner room on the 9th floor.  It was a nice room.  Comfy bed.  Very clean!
userReviews.negative:
While the room was nice, the A/C had been turned off and it took a long time for the room to cool off.  After a long walk around DC all day, a ride up on the MARC, and then a two block walk from Camden Station, it was a bit disappointing to walk up to our room and it was hot and muggy!  If you have a room reserved for a guest, make sure the room is ready!
Also, just my opinion, but I think the bathrooms could use an update.  Step in tub to shower.  Showerhead  not positioned for tall people.  And toilet seemed to be sized for short people!  LOL!
Guests came up on the 9th floor and was making a lot of noise, totally ignoring the "quiet area" sign.  I am all about having a good time, but people should be respectful to other guests!

name: La Quinta by Wyndham Inner Harbor Downtown
description:
You're eligible for a Genius discount at La Quinta by Wyndham Inner Harbor Downtown! To save at this property, all you have to do is sign in.
Featuring 3-star accommodations, La Quinta by Wyndham Inner Harbor Downtown is located in Baltimore, a 12-minute walk from Sports Legends Museum at Camden Yards and 0.6 miles from Baltimore Convention Center. With a fitness center, the 3-star hotel has air-conditioned rooms with free WiFi, each with a private bathroom. The property is 1,800 feet from the city center and a 6-minute walk from The Walters Art Museum.
At the hotel, the rooms come with a desk. All rooms in La Quinta by Wyndham Inner Harbor Downtown are equipped with a flat-screen TV and a hairdryer.
The accommodation offers a buffet or continental breakfast.
La Quinta by Wyndham Inner Harbor Downtown also provides a business center and guests can use the on-site ATM machine or use the fax machine and photocopier at the hotel. Speaking English and Spanish, staff at the 24-hour front desk can help you plan your stay.
Popular points of interest near La Quinta by Wyndham Inner Harbor Downtown include University of Maryland – Baltimore, Historic Ships in Baltimore and Edgar Allen Poe Museum. The nearest airport is Baltimore - Washington International Airport, 9.3 miles from the accommodation.

name: Days Inn by Wyndham Baltimore Inner Harbor
description:
You're eligible for a Genius discount at Days Inn by Wyndham Baltimore Inner Harbor! To save at this property, all you have to do is sign in.
A quick stroll from the Baltimore Convention Center and located in the heart of the scenic Inner Harbor area, Days Inn by Wyndham Baltimore Inner Harbor features an on-site restaurant, bar, and in-room amenities.
All guest rooms feature in-room microwaves, refrigerators and flat-screen cable TVs. Start your day off with a free continental breakfast together with coffee, tea and juice. Served Daily 6:30am-9:30am.
Guests enjoy free wireless internet and a fitness center. Onsite parking is available  for a fee of $34.00 per day. Meeting rooms are also available.
The Days Inn by Wyndham Baltimore Inner Harbor is 2,100 feet from the Oriole Park at Camden Yards, home to professional baseball's Orioles. The National Aquarium as well as a number of shopping centers and restaurants are within a 0.6 mi radius.

userReviews.title: A clean hotel in a good location; But nasty surprises can happen.
userReviews.positive: The location of the hotel is not bad for Baltimore. 5 minutes walking distance to Hilton and Convention Center. Room size and cleanliness is good. There is an iron and 5-6 kinds of towels of different sizes in the room. The breakfast is satisfactory.
userReviews.negative:
No slippers in the room. The device that regulates the room temperature is very noisy. But these are nothing. Look at the main problem...
First of all, let me say that most of the employees are helpful and friendly. I did not have any problems with the reception staff, the floor staff or the staff in the restaurant; I even became friends with some of them because I stayed for 1 week. On the last day (20.11.2022), when I was checking out in the morning, I REQUESTED a young lady at the reception to call me a taxi. This lady sullenly said she couldn't call a taxi, that's not her job (???). Then she handed me a card and said you can call it from here if you want, and went to the inner room with the open door and tried to sleep on the chair (???). Since there was a problem with my phone and I did not know the address information correctly, I asked him to help me again. She looked at me with an angry and hopeless look and said she couldn't do that. After all, the taxi I called took the order in a sleepy voice and said she would come in 10-15 minutes. After waiting 30 minutes, I called him again and he picked up the phone and hung up without answering. When I called again, he had now completely turned off his phone. On the same day, there was a game in the city and the traffic was heavy. It was very difficult to find a taxi. I went in front of the Hilton with my 2 big suitcases, I was able to find a taxi from there. But when I went to the train station, my train to Philadelphia had already left ))) The behavior of this lady, who was on duty on the last day, for no reason, destroyed my ideas about the establishment. Second time I will never stay at this hotel. After all, we do not know in advance what kind of person will be on duty when we need help.
userReviews.room: Queen Room with Bath Tub - Mobility Accessible/Non-Smoking

name: Hyatt Regency Baltimore
description:
Located in Baltimore’s Inner Harbor, this hotel features an on-site restaurant and lounge, as well as an outdoor swimming pool. The National Aquarium, Baltimore is 5 minutes’ walk away.
The Hyatt Regency Baltimore features rooms with a flat-screen cable TV and a coffee maker. The rooms are all equipped with WiFi. Select rooms have views of the Harbor.
Bistro 300 serves breakfast, lunch, and dinner and offers local dishes including Maryland crab cakes. Bistro 300 Lounge has drinks and a bar menu.
Guests can relax on the sun terrace by the pool or visit the 24-hour fitness center. Concierge services are available.
M&T Bank Stadium, home of the Baltimore Ravens football team, is 15 minutes’ walk away. The Sports Legends Museum at Camden Yards is 10 minutes’ walk away.

name: Sleep Inn & Suites Downtown Inner Harbor
description:
In a historic warehouse with a gym and free Wi-Fi, this eco-friendly Baltimore hotel is blocks from downtown Inner Harbor.  Shot Tower Metro Station is 0.3 miles away.
Guest rooms at the Sleep Inn & Suites Downtown Inner Harbor provide a 32-inch flat-screen cable TV and coffee facilities. Each air-conditioned room includes ironing facilities and guests can make free local telephone calls.
A business center with fax and photocopying services is available at the hotel. Downtown Inner Harbor Sleep Inn & Suites also offers on-site laundry facilities.
Johns Hopkins Hospital is a half-mile from Sleep Inn & Suites Downtown Inner Harbor. The National Aquarium is a 10 minute walk from the hotel.

The Maryland Zoo in Baltimore is 3.5 miles away. The Washington Monument & Museum is an 8-minute walk from the hotel.

name: Lord Baltimore Hotel
description:
You're eligible for a Genius discount at Lord Baltimore Hotel! To save at this property, all you have to do is sign in.
Located in the city center of Baltimore, this hotel is 2,100 feet to the Inner Harbor and is 3,150 feet drive to Oriole Park at Camden Yards. Free Wi-Fi is accessible.
Guests staying at the Lord Baltimore can enjoy on-site features like a restaurant, a business center and a fitness center. The property also features LB Skybar, a rooftop bar, open on selected days of the week with views of Baltimore and music.
Each room at the Lord Baltimore Hotel features amenities like plush bedding, a 40-inch flat-screen cable TV and a coffee machine. Free toiletries are supplied in the private bathroom.
The Charles Center rail station is steps away from the hotel. Baltimore Convention Center and M&T Bank Stadium are within 0.9 mi of the hotel.

name: Delta Hotels by Marriott Baltimore Inner Harbor
description:
In a prime location in the center of Baltimore, Delta Hotels by Marriott Baltimore Inner Harbor provides air-conditioned rooms, a fitness center, free WiFi and a restaurant. This 4-star hotel offers a 24-hour front desk and an ATM. Baltimore Convention Center is a 6-minute walk from the hotel and University of Maryland – Baltimore is 0.6 miles away.
At the hotel, every room includes a desk, a TV, a private bathroom, bed linen and towels. All guest rooms feature a closet.
Guests at Delta Hotels by Marriott Baltimore Inner Harbor can enjoy an American breakfast.
Guests can use the business center or relax in the bar.
Popular points of interest near the accommodation include Historic Ships in Baltimore, The Walters Art Museum and Sports Legends Museum at Camden Yards. The nearest airport is Baltimore - Washington International Airport, 9.3 miles from Delta Hotels by Marriott Baltimore Inner Harbor.

name: Kimpton Hotel Monaco Baltimore Inner Harbor, an IHG Hotel
description:
This pet-friendly Baltimore hotel is located 10 minutes’ walk from the Inner Harbor and features an on-site restaurant and bar. The Baltimore Convention Center is 5 minutes’ walk away.
Each modern room at the Kimpton Hotel Monaco Baltimore Inner Harbor features a flat-screen TV, fully stocked mini-bar, and an iHome docking station. Some suites have a spa bath and a living area with sofa bed.
B&O Restaurant is an award-winning American Brasserie serving breakfast, lunch, and dinner. The lounge area has a variety of drinks and light fare.
Wi-Fi access is available for guests at the Kimpton Hotel Monaco Baltimore Inner Harbor. An onsite fitness center is available. Dry cleaning services are also provided. Coffee and tea are served every morning and a wine hour is hosted each evening.
Camden Yards and M&T Bank Stadium are within 1 miles of the hotel. The National Aquarium, Baltimore is 10 minutes’ walk away.

name: Staybridge Suites Baltimore - Inner Harbor, an IHG Hotel
description:
Located in Baltimore, 1,300 feet from National Aquarium in Baltimore, Staybridge Suites Baltimore - Inner Harbor features air-conditioned rooms with free WiFi throughout the property.
Each room includes a flat-screen TV and a fully equipped kitchen. You will find a coffee machine in the room. All rooms are fitted with a private bathroom fitted with a bath or shower. Extras include free toiletries and a hairdryer.
You will find a 24-hour front desk at the property. A complimentary breakfast buffet is offered. Valet parking is available at a surcharge.
The Baltimore Convention Center is 2,800 feet from Staybridge Suites Baltimore - Inner, while Oriole Park at Camden Yards is 0.8 mi away. Hard Rock Cafe is 1,950 feet away and Pier Six Pavilion is 3,100 feet away. Baltimore - Washington International Airport is 11 mi from the property.

name: Comfort Inn & Suites Baltimore Inner Harbor
description:
You're eligible for a Genius discount at Comfort Inn & Suites Baltimore Inner Harbor! To save at this property, all you have to do is sign in.
This modern and contemporary hotel is centrally located in the heart of Baltimore, just 350 feet from the Inner Harbor. Facilities include WiFi access. The National Aquarium of Baltimore is 8 minutes’ walk away.
The Comfort Inn & Suites Baltimore Inner Harbor are modern and offer cable TV, refrigerators, microwaves, coffee-making facilities, and private bathrooms with free toiletries. Select suites offer a separate seating area with sofa bed.
An on-site business center and laundry facilities are provided.
Tour the USS Constellation battleship, just 5 minutes’ walk from the hotel. The Sports Legends Museum, Camden Yards, and M&T Bank Stadium are all 2,650 feet away.

name: Candlewood Suites Baltimore - Inner Harbor, an IHG Hotel
description:
Set in the heart of Baltimore, Candlewood Suites Baltimore - Inner Harbor is a 7-minute walk from Lexington Market. Featuring a fitness center, the hotel is close to several noted attractions, around 1,950 feet from Baltimore Convention Center and around 2,300 feet from Historic Ships in Baltimore. The property is an 8-minute walk from The Walters Art Museum.
The rooms at the hotel come with a seating area and a flat-screen TV with cable channels. With a private bathroom fitted with a bath or shower and a hair dryer, rooms at Candlewood Suites Baltimore also have free WiFi. All units at the accommodations include air conditioning and a desk.
Staff at the 24-hour front desk can help guests with any queries that they may have.
Top of the World Observation Level is an 8-minute walk from the hotel. The nearest airport is Baltimore - Washington International Airport, 8.1 mi from the property.

name: Hampton Inn & Suites Baltimore Inner Harbor
description:
This Maryland hotel is located 2 blocks from Baltimore's Historic Inner Harbor and the Baltimore Convention Center. The hotel offers a hot breakfast, indoor pool and spacious guest rooms.
Hampton Inn Baltimore Inner Harbor guest rooms are furnished with a large work desk and in-room coffee maker. Cable TV and free Wi-Fi are also provided.
Guests at the Baltimore Hampton Inn can work out in the gym or use the business center. Safety deposit boxes are available at the front desk and a convenience store is located on site.
Hampton Inn and Suites Inner Harbor Baltimore is within a 5-minute walk of Port Discovery and the Maryland Science Center. M & T Bank Stadium, home of the Baltimore Ravens football team, is just one mile away.

A complaint was made to front desk about the huge (at least 20+ young adults) party next door to us. 
Nothing was done to follow up and have them stop!  The hallway and room next to ours had people smoking weed, drinking, laughing, yelling, banging on doors, walls etc.  At one point there were 5 young girls directly outside our door, leaning up against our door.  The door was constantly banging, we were kept awake and had to keep the pup quiet!! 
When I went down to front desk to have it addressed,  there were 10 young people coming from the room next to us!  TEN!  And that wasn't even close to the number of people left in the hallway and the room
The noise could be heard clearly from the elevator so there would be no excuse as to why hotel staff "didn't hear it" once arriving on the third floor. 
Nothing was addressed about the noise or the number of people in the room and hallway.  The smell from the weed was rank in the hallway and into our room.

name: Hampton Inn Baltimore Bayview Campus
description:
Featuring 3-star accommodations, Hampton Inn Baltimore Bayview Campus is located in Baltimore, 2.9 miles from Korean War Memorial and 3.5 miles from Fell's Point. With free WiFi, this 3-star hotel offers a 24-hour front desk and an ATM. Free private parking is available and the hotel also provides a shuttle service for guests who want to explore the surrounding area.
At the hotel, each room has a desk. Complete with a private bathroom equipped with a bath or shower and a hairdryer, guest rooms at Hampton Inn Baltimore Bayview Campus have a flat-screen TV and air conditioning, and selected rooms come with a seating area. All guest rooms will provide guests with a fridge.
The accommodation offers a buffet or American breakfast.
Harbor East Marina is 3.9 miles from Hampton Inn Baltimore Bayview Campus, while Pier Six Concert Pavilion is 3.9 miles away. The nearest airport is Martin State Airport, 9.3 miles from the hotel.

userReviews.title: A shadow of its former glorious hotel - bitterly disappointed for the price
userReviews.positive: The Inn at the Colonnade is the default place to stay for visitors to Johns Hopkins University and the famous Space Telescope Science Institute. Within walking distance of both, it's an obvious choice. I stayed there numerous times in the 1990s and early 2000s and enjoyed its spacious rooms and wonderful restaurant. This was my first visit since the pandemic and I was shocked to see how the place has deteriorated as a first class hotel.
userReviews.negative: In the following I don't wish to complain about any of the Colonnade staff who were welcoming and helpful. However, I simply couldn't believe how the former excellent restaurant area has been reconfigured into a basic "cafeteria-style" open-plan area contiguous with the lobby where, had I wished to enjoy an evening meal, I'd be basically sitting in  full view of the bar and arriving guests. No privacy, no style. As I stood waiting to be seated, the waiter thrust a menu in my general direction as he hurried to simultaneously serve people in the bar. When I asked at reception whether there were suitable restaurants nearby, she sighed in sympathy and admitted the place has suffered greatly due to the pandemic. The bedrooms are still luxurious and spacious but why pretend this place is a first class hotel and charge the same when it has clearly gone downhill - disappointed and poor value for money. For this price it desperately needs a proper restaurant, not something like one witnesses at cheap airport hotels.
userReviews.room: Queen Room with Two Queen Beds - Non-Smoking

description:
This Baltimore hotel is only 10 minutes' drive from the center of downtown. The hotel offers a gym, large business center and on-site dining. Rooms are equipped with microwaves and refrigerators.
Every guest room at the Best Western Baltimore Hotel features free Wi-Fi and cable TV with in-room movies. A work desk and a lounge chair are also provided.

Baltimore Hotel and Conference Center Best Western provides a hot breakfast every morning. Additional dining includes the Tradewinds Restaurant and Lounge and Baltimore Comedy Factory.
Baltimore Best Western Hotel is only a 10-minute drive from local attractions including M&T Bank Stadium, National Aquarium, the University of Maryland and Baltimore Convention Center.

userReviews.title: Wonderful
userReviews.positive:
The location can't be beat being in the middle of Charles Village next to JHU's campus and the hospital. I have easy access to the CityLink/LocalLink bus lines and the Charm City Circulator. It's too far east to be close to the Light Rail. I also liked using the porch to relax and sit outside on the ledge at night after work or during the early mornings before I leave. The King sized bed was SO comfy and easy to maneuver in that I'm thinking about getting one for myself when I moved into my next apartment. I loved that there was storage (empty 3-drawer dresser and a full-sized closet), laundry facilities and plenty of seating areas on the first floor and the basement. 
It's the perfect place to use as a base of operations when traveling just to have as a place to store your stuff or if you're like me and have to commute to Baltimore for work. I work the night schedule and can't get back home on late nights because the Marc is shut down by 10-10:30pm and the LightRail doesn't go far enough south to be useful beyond going to Glen Burnie or BWI. I live in Crofton, MD, so there's no easy way to get home from Baltimore, so I have to commute using whatever I have at my disposal.
userReviews.negative:
The electronic keypad locks were a challenge on the first night to figure out after a having a long day at work. Sometimes I mix up numbers in my head like a mild form of dyscalculia (number or math dyslexia), so it took some time and patience. Thankfully, the host was very responsive and patient with me at 10-11pm at night.
I wish there were paper towels for quick clean ups/spills and a dish drying rack for washing dishes. I also wished that there were drinking glasses (not just a plethora of coffee mugs), oven mitts, and at least one cookie sheet available to easily heat up foods. Certain foods requires an oven to maintain the crispness, but I only had access to a flimsy, disposable and dirty aluminum pan that looked like it was used to catch water from a leaky faucet than to cook food in. Only had dirty, used white towel to use as makeshift oven mitt which got tricky when trying to get the flimsy pan out of the oven because it easily bent and lost its shape holding it from the middle because I didn't have two oven mitts to easily hold the pan by its edges. It was a very near thang, because I ended up dropping some of my food on the floor.

name: Courtyard Baltimore Downtown/McHenry Row
description:
Featuring 3-star accommodations, Courtyard Baltimore Downtown/McHenry Row is located in Baltimore, 1.4 miles from Inner Harbor and 2.1 miles from Historic Ships in Baltimore. Featuring a fitness center, the 3-star hotel has air-conditioned rooms with free WiFi, each with a private bathroom. Guests can enjoy American dishes at the restaurant or have a drink at the bar.
At the hotel, rooms have a desk. The rooms have a flat-screen TV, and some accommodations at Courtyard Baltimore Downtown/McHenry Row have a city view. At the accommodation the rooms include bed linen and towels.
À la carte and American breakfast options are available each morning at Courtyard Baltimore Downtown/McHenry Row.
For guests' convenience, the hotel has a business center. Staff at Courtyard Baltimore Downtown/McHenry Row are available to give advice at the 24-hour front desk.
Baltimore Convention Center is 2.4 miles from the accommodation, while Pier Six Concert Pavilion is 2.8 miles from the property. The nearest airport is Baltimore - Washington International Airport, 9.3 miles from Courtyard Baltimore Downtown/McHenry Row.

userReviews.title: As good as advertised, worth the stay!

They also allowed me to keep the lone iron and ironing board as long as I needed it. (Apparently few other guests ever request them ) The property itself was convenient to public transportation (several bus lines and one light rail station), as well as my intended destination, Oriole Park at Camden Yards. There are a variety of eateries (China Wok, Korean Barbecue, The Empanada Lady, McDonald's, to name a few) in the vicinity, as well as a gas station / convenience store, Lucky Supermarket, and pharmacy in the vicinity of Graffiti Alley (19th 1/2 St). The surrounding area may seem daunting to some, but it's mostly sprawling and scarcely occupied. Motel 6 Baltimore Downtown itself is a veritable oasis. I would gladly stay there again.

name: The Inn at Henderson's Wharf, Ascend Hotel Collection
description:
The Inn at Henderson’s Wharf, an Ascend Hotel Collection Member, offers a tranquil retreat located directly on the waterfront of Baltimore’s historic Fell’s Point just steps away from boutique shops, upscale pubs and fine dining, yet nestled quietly on the end of a cobblestone street. This hotel offers easy access to popular attractions like the National Aquarium in Baltimore, Discovery Children’s Museum and Oriole Park in Camden Yards. Butler Service is offered.
Other nearby points of interest include, the Baltimore Convention Center, Top of the World Observation and Edgar Allen Poe’s House.
Guests of the hotel will appreciate exceptional style and service, as well as luxurious details that blend old-world charm with new-world comfort. The fitness center is a great place to work out. Business travelers will appreciate the business center. There are three meeting rooms, with the hotel able to accommodate 60 people for banquets and conferences.
The hotel service fee includes coffee available in the lobby 24 hours, high-speed Internet access, bottled water, unlimited local and domestic long distance calls, computer and printing access, incoming and outgoing fax service, photocopy services and a weekday newspaper. A guest pass to the MAC fitness center and pool, exclusive Harbor Magic events and Harbor Magic shuttle service is also included with the service fee.
Each designer room is appointed with the finest furnishings and amenities, including robes, a flat-screen television with iPod jacks, coffee maker, desk, hair dryer, iron and ironing board.
This is a nonsmoking hotel.

description:

All guest rooms at the hotel are equipped with a seating area, refrigerator and flat-screen TV. Some rooms will provide you with a kitchen with a dishwasher and a microwave.
An American breakfast is served daily at the property. At Residence Inn Johns Hopkins Medical you will find a restaurant serving American cuisine.
The accommodations offers a business center for guest use.
Johns Hopkins Hospital is a 7-minute walk from the hotel, while Power Plant is 1.3 mi away. The nearest airport is Baltimore - Washington International Airport, 9.3 mi from Residence Inn Johns Hopkins Medical.

name: Sagamore Pendry Baltimore
description:
Offering a seasonal outdoor pool, Sagamore Pendry Baltimore is located in the Fells Point district in Baltimore. Set at the waters edge, an open-air courtyard allows guests an outdoor lush space while the private pool deck offers a seasonal bar and grill with outdoor dining and lounging,
Rooms include a flat-screen TV. Certain units feature a seating area for your convenience. Some rooms have views of the pool or garden. Each room is fitted with a private bathroom. For your comfort, you will find bathrobes, free toiletries and a hairdryer.
There is a 24-hour front desk, 24-hour fitness center, a cash machine, a shared lounge and gift shop at the property. The hotel features two on-site restaurants, Rec Pier Chophouse and The Cannon Room, helmed by chef Andrew Carmellini. Sagamore Pendry Baltimore also offers function rooms to host board meetings, gatherings and weddings.
The hotel also offers car hire. Harbor East Marina is 2,650 feet from Sagamore Pendry Baltimore, while Pier Six Concert Pavillion is 0.7 mi from the property. The nearest airport is Baltimore - Washington International Airport, 8.1 mi from the property.

name: Admiral Fell Inn Baltimore Harbor, Ascend Hotel Collection
description:
Baltimore's historic Fell's Point neighborhood is home to this charming hotel, located steps from the waterfront and other attractions, and offering unique accommodations and thoughtful amenities.
Many activities and attractions can be found close to the Admiral Fell Inn Baltimore Harbor, Ascend Hotel Collection, including Maritime Park, scenic boat rides and exciting ghost tours. A variety of restaurants and unique shops are also only a short distance away.
Admiral Fell Inn Baltimore Harbor, Ascend Hotel Collection elegantly blends 18th century furnishings with many modern amenities, including wireless internet and in-room coffeemakers. Completely nonsmoking accommodations also feature on-demand movies.

name: Canopy By Hilton Baltimore Harbor Point - Newly Built
description:
Located in Baltimore, a 8-minute walk from Harbor East Marina, Canopy By Hilton Baltimore Harbor Point - Newly Built provides accommodations with free bikes, private parking, a fitness center and a terrace. Among the facilities of this property are a restaurant, room service and a 24-hour front desk, along with free WiFi throughout the property. Guests can have a drink at the bar.
All guest rooms will provide guests with a fridge.
À la carte and American breakfast options are available daily at the hotel.
You can play pool at this 4-star hotel.
Popular points of interest near Canopy By Hilton Baltimore Harbor Point - Newly Built include Fell's Point, Pier Six Concert Pavilion and Historic Ships in Baltimore. The nearest airport is Baltimore - Washington International Airport, 10 miles from the accommodation.

name: Courtyard by Marriott Baltimore Downtown/Inner Harbor
description:
Just 1 block away from Baltimore’s scenic waterfront, Courtyard Downtown/Inner Harbor is located a 10-minute walk from the National Aquarium. It features a well-equipped gym.
Rooms at the Courtyard by Marriott Baltimore Downtown/Inner Harbor offer complimentary WiFi access and have large windows and spacious seating areas. Each is equipped with a working station featuring conveniently placed lighting and ergonomic chair.
Guests can enjoy refreshing options for breakfast or dinner with cocktails at The Bistro. There are numerous lively restaurants and bars that surround the property. On site vending machines for drinks and snacks are also available.
Many of Baltimore’s Inner Harbor attractions, including Fells Point and Little Italy are less than a 10-minute walk away from the Courtyard Downtown hotel.

name: The Ivy Hotel
description:
Built in 1889, this 5-star boutique hotel features a luxury spa and fine dining restaurant. Located in the Mount Vernon neighborhood of Baltimore, The Ivy Hotel is 0.6 mi from the Walters Art Museum.
Each suite or guestroom in this posh mansion includes a four-poster bed, plush bedding, a gas fireplace and heated limestone floors in the bathrooms. Some suites have a view of Mount Vernon and a balcony.
The Ivy Hotel has a courtyard with leafy walls where guests can enjoy a pot of tea. The Spa at the Ivy offers an extensive treatment selection and in-room massages as well.
The Magdalena offers unique culinary creations that focus on local ingredients and seasonal cuisine. The upscale bistro can be enjoyed Tuesday through Sunday for dinner.
John Hopkins University and the Baltimore Convention Center are 1.2 mi from the hotel. The Inner Harbor and Oriole Park at Camden Yards are just 5 minutes ride from The Ivy Hotel Baltimore.

name: Tru By Hilton Baltimore Harbor East
description:
You're eligible for a Genius discount at Tru By Hilton Baltimore Harbor East! To save at this property, all you have to do is sign in.
Located in Baltimore and with Harbor East Marina reachable within a 7-minute walk, Tru By Hilton Baltimore Harbor East provides concierge services, non-smoking rooms, a fitness center, free WiFi throughout the property and a shared lounge. This 3-star hotel offers a 24-hour front desk and a business center. Guests can have a drink at the snack bar.
Guests at the hotel can enjoy a buffet or an American breakfast.
Popular points of interest near Tru By Hilton Baltimore Harbor East include Pier Six Concert Pavilion, Historic Ships in Baltimore and Fell's Point. The nearest airport is Baltimore - Washington International Airport, 10 miles from the accommodation.

name: Four Seasons Baltimore
description:
This 5-star luxury hotel located in Baltimore’s Inner Harbor features free Wi-Fi, full service spa, rooftop infinity pool, and 4 on-site dining facilities. The National Aquarium is 0.6 mi away.
The modernly decorated guest rooms at the Four Seasons Baltimore include floor-to-ceiling windows, a flat-screen TV, and a marble bathroom with deep soaking tub and walk-in rain shower.
Guests can visit the state-of-the-art fitness center and sauna. Seasonal cabana rentals are available for poolside relaxation at the Baltimore Four Seasons. The business center is open 24-hours.
Atlas Restaurant Group's Maximón serves Latin American cuisine and is open for breakfast, lunch and dinner. Located on the 29th floor and offering city views, The Bygone is open for dinner and Sunday brunch.
Camden Yards and M&T Bank Stadium are within 1.9 mi of the hotel. The historic neighborhood of Fell’s Point is 2,650 feet away.

name: Hilton Garden Inn Baltimore Inner Harbor
description:
Located in the heart of Baltimore's Harbor East neighborhood and adjacent to vibrant Little Italy, this hotel provides state-of-the-art amenities and facilities, including an on-site restaurant and free Wi-Fi.
The Hilton Garden Inn Baltimore Inner Harbor is located in the center of all the action. Walk to nearby attractions including the National Aquarium, Camden Yards and Fell's Points. Stroll along the charming waterfront and discover unique shops, gourmet restaurants and an exciting nightlife.
Guestrooms at the Baltimore Inner Harbor Hilton Garden Inn are furnished with all the latest technologies. Guests can watch a film on a flat-screen TV, brew coffee with the Keurig coffee machine, or take advantage of the in-room microwave and refrigerator. Enjoy on-site dining at the Great American Grill, or grab something to go from the Pavilion Pantry convenience store.

name: Homewood Suites by Hilton Baltimore
description:
Situated in the heart of Baltimore's Inner Harbor and close to area attractions, this all-suite hotel provides guests with many of the comforts of home, including fully equipped kitchens.
The Homewood Suites Baltimore is within walking distance to many popular sites. The charming Little Italy neighborhood, the National Aquarium and numerous boutiques and restaurants are only steps away.

userReviews.title: Great stay, great location, best staff
userReviews.positive: The location was excellent, we all felt safe around the hotel during the day and in the hotel at night. We walked everywhere we went and the walks werent very long. The staff were all some of the nicest hotel staff we have ever dealt with. The morning breakfast staff was deffinately the most attentive, nicest and helpful we have ever seen in a hotels breakfast area! The bar tender/waitress in the restaurant was very nice, and even though she was by herself she did an amazing job even with a full bar! (Everywheres is understaffed right now so deffinately no complaining on that here) She handled being by herself like a pro, and we didnt have that long of a wait for our drinks! If we find ourselves staying in the area again this will definately be our choice of hotel!
userReviews.negative: The only problem we had was getting some extra blankets because some of my family gets colder than others. The night staff was having a hard time finding blankets and kept giving us sheets, we got the blankets without issue the next morning/day. Our heater was also not working but a quick call and maintenence had it fixed very quickly!  The card readers in the elevators and our room were a bit temperamental but it wasn't a huge problem!  Some things could use an update but, I was very happy with everything within the hotel and the room!
userReviews.room: One-Bedroom Double Suite with Two Double Beds and Sofa Bed - Non-Smoking

Pretty view of downtown.
userReviews.negative: Parking was a bit of a hassle, but that will always be the case with an urban hotel that doesn’t have a dedicated parking garage. Staff was perhaps TOO attentive, as we received MULTIPLE text messages during our two-night stay, asking us how everything was. Felt the price was a bit high compared to the quality of amenities in similar hotels in Baltimore.

name: Baltimore Marriott Waterfront
description:
This Baltimore hotel is located directly next to the Baltimore Harbor, in the Harbor East neighborhood. Free WiFi is available in public areas.
Guest rooms at the Baltimore Marriott Waterfront include cable TV with movie channels and pay-per-view movies. A work desk is also included.
The on-site American restaurant, Apropoe's, serves seasonal, local comfort food.
A fitness center with cardio equipment and a full-service business center are available at the Marriott Waterfront Baltimore. Over 80,000 square feet of event space is also available at the property. The hotel offers concierge services.
The National Aquarium is 10 minutes' walk away, while the Maryland Zoo is 11 minutes' drive away. Guests can explore the waterfront area by foot or water taxi.
